StringUtil.replaceAll() does not work on Strings with \ generated from a Stream. I consume json data from a web service.

protected void readResponse(InputStream input) throws IOException {
    ByteArrayOutputStream bos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
    Util.copy(input, bos);
    String s = bos.toString();
    s = StringUtil.replaceAll(s, &quot;\u0026&quot;, &quot;&amp;&quot;);

Similarly for json special characters:
&quot;\u0027&quot;, &quot;'&quot;
&quot;\u003c&quot;, &quot;&lt;&quot;
&quot;\u003d&quot;, &quot;=&quot;
&quot;\u003e&quot;, &quot;&gt;&quot;

Anything characters appearing after double quote &quot; (\&quot;) from json is truncated.

