Original [issue 1141](https://code.google.com/p/codenameone/issues/detail?id=1141) created by codenameone on 2014-06-20T13:13:17.000Z:

When drawing lines and polygons with asyncPaint=true (on Android), the alpha transparency is ignored.

I think the problem is in the class AndroidGraphics, method setColor(). It is actually implemented as

```
void setColor(int color){
    this.paint.setColor(0xff000000 | color);
    this.font.setColor(0xff000000 | color);
}
```

It should instead be implemented as

```
void setColor(int color){
    this.paint.setColor((paint.getAlpha() &lt;&lt; 24) | (color &amp; 0xffffff));
    this.font.setColor((font.getAlpha() &lt;&lt; 24) | (color &amp; 0xffffff));
}
```

or else the alpha value is lost when setAlpha() is invoked before setColor(), which the new pipeline is doing at many places.

