The MapComponent's pinch zoom behaviour is currently quite choppy.   This is because it always keeps the same map center point before, during, and after the zoom operation without any regard to where the pinch zoom is actually occurring.  This means that if the person is not pinch zooming directly in the center of the map, they will be taken to a completely different part of the map when the pointer is released.

Below is a diff that fixes this issue by keeping making sure that the coordinate of the pinch zoom (or at least the middle of it) remains in the same pixel position before, during, and after the pinch zoom operation.  

