Original [issue 914](https://code.google.com/p/codenameone/issues/detail?id=914) created by codenameone on 2013-10-10T13:51:35.000Z:

I thought I had entered this before, but did not see it - sorry if this is a dup or was rejected.

If you call new TextArea(str)  where String str == null, you get an NPE as it tries to measure the length of the null string

From TextArea.java:

   /**
     \* Creates an area with the given text, this constructor
     \* will create a single line text area similar to a text field! 
     \* 
     \* @param text the text to be displayed; if text is null, the empty 
     \* string &quot;&quot; will be displayed
     */
    public TextArea(String text) {
        this(text, Math.max(defaultMaxSize, text.length()), 1, 3, ANY);
    }

quick fix:

```
public TextArea(String text){
    String use = ((text == null)?&quot;&quot;:text);
    this(use, Math.max(defaultMaxSize, use.length()), 1, 3, ANY);
}
```

